HEADWORD: Sodality
<hw>So*dal"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Sodalities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>sodalitas</ets>,
fr. <ets>sodalis</ets> a comrade.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fellowship
or fraternity; a brotherhood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>Specifically, a lay
association for devotion or for charitable purposes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sodamide</ent>⟦br⟧
